[31]. Secondly, we compare the previously collected DNS records with the CDN-assigned subdomains (see Table 2) to identify the domains hosted on the CDN. Thirdly, we send HTTP requests to the identified domains hosted by the CDN. We then compare their responses with non-CDN-deployed fingerprints (see Table 3) to recheck the domains hosted by the CDN. This process ensures the accuracy of our results, clearly distinguishing between CDN-deployed and non-CDN-deployed domains thereby reducing false positives.

